  "prompt": "Does every student at iiser get fellowship?",
  "response": "Indian Institutes of Science Education and Research (IISERs) typically offer fellowships to their students, particularly those enrolled in the integrated BS-MS programs, PhD programs, and other research-oriented courses. The fellowship amounts and eligibility criteria may vary depending on the specific program and the student's academic performance.\n\nFor BS-MS students, the fellowship is usually provided by the Ministry of Human Resource Development (MHRD) or other government bodies, subject to fulfilling certain academic requirements and maintaining a specified grade point average (GPA). PhD students often receive a stipend that covers their living expenses, which is provided by the institute or through external funding sources like research grants.\n\nIt is always advisable to check the specific fellowship policies directly with the IISER you are interested in, as they can vary and are subject to change.",
